cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.DC 

The paper discusses Multi-User Detection (MUD) techniques in the context of satellite communication systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), communication and information theory (cs.COMM), systems and control (cs.SY), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also evaluates the performance of the proposed system, which involves simulation and modeling (cs.SY) and performance evaluation and optimization (cs.DC).
